  "prompt": "What is the meaning of sending nudge in hike messenger?",
  "response": "In Hike Messenger, sending a \"nudge\" is a way to get the attention of the person you're messaging. It's similar to a \"poke\" on Facebook or a \"nudge\" in other messaging apps. When you send a nudge, it typically sends a notification or vibrates the recipient's phone, prompting them to check your message. This feature is useful when you want to ensure that the person notices your message, especially if it's urgent or if they haven't responded to previous messages.",
